╭─ Assistant [MainThread@565839] ───────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ Here is the final patch implementing a robust fix for the crash by enforcing  │
│ SCEV availability preconditions before querying ScalarEvolution for           │
│ loop-entry guarded conditions, and by constraining SCEV expansion to safe     │
│ insertion points.                                                             │
│                                                                               │
│ Patch summary:                                                                │
│ - In LoopPredication::expandCheck:                                            │
│   - Rewrites both SCEVs to the innermost scope with SE->getSCEVAtScope to     │
│ avoid referencing values not dominating the loop preheader.                   │
│   - Adds availability checks before calling SE->isLoopEntryGuardedByCond. If  │
│ the operands are not available at loop entry, it falls back to materializing  │
│ the compare.                                                                  │
│ - In LoopPredication::findInsertPt (SCEV variant):                            │
│   - Requires both loop invariance and availability at loop entry before       │
│ choosing the preheader as the insertion point; otherwise, it expands at the   │
│ use to avoid dominance violations.                                            │
│                                                                               │
│ Files modified:                                                               │
│ - llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/LoopPredication.cpp                              │
│                                                                               │
│ Diff (conceptual):                                                            │
│ - expandCheck:                                                                │
│   - Inserted:                                                                 │
│     LHS = SE->getSCEVAtScope(LHS, L);                                         │
│     RHS = SE->getSCEVAtScope(RHS, L);                                         │
│   - Replaced simple loop-invariance check with:                               │
│     if (SE->isLoopInvariant(LHS, L) && SE->isLoopInvariant(RHS, L)) {         │
│       if (SE->isAvailableAtLoopEntry(LHS, L) &&                               │
│ SE->isAvailableAtLoopEntry(RHS, L)) {                                         │
│         ... isLoopEntryGuardedByCond ...                                      │
│       }                                                                       │
│     }                                                                         │
│ - findInsertPt(const SCEVExpander&, Instruction*, ArrayRef<const SCEV*>):     │
│   - Now requires SE->isAvailableAtLoopEntry(Op, L) in addition to             │
│ SE->isLoopInvariant(Op, L) and Expander.isSafeToExpandAt.                     │
│                                                                               │
│ Rationale:                                                                    │
│ - ScalarEvolution::isLoopEntryGuardedByCond asserts that both operands are    │
│ available at loop entry. LoopPredication previously only checked loop         │
│ invariance and could violate this precondition, triggering the assertion in   │
│ cases where SCEV operands involve values from other loops or non-dominating   │
│ definitions (as in the reproducer with an atomic load from a different loop). │
│ - getSCEVAtScope normalizes SCEVs to the loop scope and prevents expanding    │
│ expressions which reference non-dominating values.                            │
│ - Strengthening findInsertPt ensures we do not introduce IR which fails       │
│ dominance due to expansion at the preheader when the SCEV isn't actually      │
│ available at loop entry.                                                      │
│                                                                               │
│ Please apply the patch and re-run the test pipeline.                          │
