│ 515   // loop-unswitch or loop-peeling to make progress on examples with lots │
│ of                                                                            │
│ 516   // predicable range checks in a row.  (Since, in the general case,  we  │
│ can't                                                                         │
│ 517   // hoist the length checks until the dominating checks have been        │
│ discharged                                                                    │
│ 518   // as we can't prove doing so is safe.)                                 │
│ 519   // 2) As a nice side effect, this exposes the value of peeling or       │
│ unswitching                                                                   │
│ 520   // much more obviously in the IR.  Otherwise, the cost modeling for     │
